<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10351320>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1−6. 1. Pronotum of Atlanticolycus camposgerais sp. nov.; 2–6. Habitus: 2. A. camposgerais; 3. A. japi sp. nov.; 4. A. itatiaia sp. nov.; 5. A. ilhabela sp. nov.; 6. A. morretes sp. nov. Scales: Fig. 1: 0.5 mm, Figs. 2–6: 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10351320/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10351324>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7−18. Genitalia: 7–16. Aedeagi lateral and ventral views: 7–8. A. camposgerais sp. nov.; 9–10. A. japi sp. nov.; 11–12. A. itatiaia sp. nov. (stained with Chlorazol Black); 13–14. A. ilhabela sp. nov.; 15–16. A. morretes sp. nov.; 17–18: female genitalia. 17. A. camposgerais; 18. A. japi. Arrows indicate the following structures: a– phallic dorsoapical projections, b– phallus apex, c– parameral thorns. Scale: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10351324/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10351326>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. Geographical distribution of Atlanticolycus species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10351326/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

